'''Big Falls''' is a [[waterfall]] located near the town of [[Terrebonne, Oregon|Terrebonne]] in [[Deschutes County, Oregon|Deschutes County]], in the [[U.S. state]] of [[Oregon]].<ref name="Northwest Waterfall Survey">{{cite web|title=Big Falls Deschutes County, Oregon|url=https://www.waterfallsnorthwest.com/waterfall/Big-Falls-3784|website=Northwest Waterfall Survey|accessdate=8 June 2017}}</ref> Big Falls is a mandatory [[portage]] on the right of the cascade. The main channel should not be approached by water craft because of the rocky nature of the riverbed.<ref name=RiverBrain>{{cite web|title=Deschutes River - Canyon Run (Lower Bridge to Billy Chinook Res.) Big Falls |url=http://www.riverbrain.com/river_rapid/show/957 |website=RiverBrain.com|accessdate=8 June 2017}}</ref> 

