'''Katannilik Territorial Park Reserve'''{{Pronunciation-needed}} ("the place of waterfalls") is a [[territorial park]] in the [[Qikiqtaaluk Region]] of [[Nunavut]], Canada. It was established in 1993 and has an area of {{convert|1262|km2|sqmi|abbr=on}}. The [[Soper River]], part of the [[Canadian Heritage Rivers System]], flows through the park.

