| {{flagicon|France}} [[French copyright law|France]]
| Life + 70 years (except posthumous works published after this term){{efn|An audiovisual work is copyrighted in France for the same term, computed from the last surviving person among the following: the author of the scenario, the author of the dialogue, the author of the musical compositions, with or without words, specially composed for the work and the main director.}}<ref name="France">{{cite web|url=http://www.wipo.int/wipolex/en/text.jsp?file_id=363403|title=France: Code de la propriété intellectuelle (version consolidée au 23 février 2015)|publisher=|accessdate=1 February 2017}}</ref>{{rp|Arts. L123-1, L123-2}}
<br>The following additions to copyright term formerly applied to all works, but the French [[Court of Cassation (France)|Cour de Cassation]] has found them to be superseded by later copyright treaties, thus limiting the copyright term to life + 70 years total, at least for non-musical works of authors who did not "die for France".<ref>Judgement No. 280 of February 27, 2007 Court of Cassation – First Civil Chamber [https://translate.google.com/translate?js=y&prev=_t&ie=UTF-8&layout=1&eotf=1&u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.courdecassation.fr%2Fjurisprudence_2%2Fpremiere_chambre_civile_568%2Farret_no_9940.html&sl=fr&tl=en 04-12138]</ref>

<br>+ [[:fr:Prorogations de guerre#Première Guerre mondiale|6 years 152 days]] for '''musical''' work published through 1920<ref name="France"/>{{rp|Art. L123-8}}
<br>+ [[:fr:Prorogations de guerre#Seconde Guerre mondiale|8 years and 120 days]] for '''musical''' work published through 1947<ref name="France"/>{{rp|Art. L123-9}}
<br>+ 30 years for all works if the author [[Mort pour la France|died on active service]]<ref name="France"/>{{rp|Art. L123-10}}
| 70 years from publication (pseudonymous, anonymous or collective works)<ref name="France"/>{{rp|Art. L123-3}}
<br>25 years from publication (posthumous works published after Art. L123-1 term)<ref name="France"/>{{rp|L123-4}}
| Yes<ref name="France"/>{{rp|Arts. L123-1, L123-3, L123-4, but not Arts. L123-8 or L123-9}}
