| Life + 70 years<ref name="GKRF_1281">{{cite web|url=http://www.consultant.ru/popular/gkrf4/ |title=Article 1281 of Civil Code |publisher=Consultant.ru |date= |accessdate=2012-06-08}}</ref>

Life + 74 years (for those who fought in or worked during the war of 1941–45)

Date of rehabilitation + 70 (74) years (for unlawfully prosecuted and posthumously [[Rehabilitation (Soviet)|rehabilitated]])

Protection applies if copyright term of Life + 50 years (or Life + 54 years) did not expire by 1 January 1993.<ref name="231-FZ">{{cite web|url=http://base.garant.ru/12151067/#6|title=Федеральный закон от 18.12.2006 N 231-ФЗ "О введении в действие части четвертой Гражданского кодекса Российской Федерации" (с изменениями и дополнениями)|publisher=|accessdate=1 February 2017}}</ref>
|50 years from publication (radio and television broadcasts)<ref name="GKRF_1330">{{cite web|url=http://www.consultant.ru/popular/gkrf4/ |title=Article 1330 of Civil Code |publisher=Consultant.ru |date= |accessdate=2014-12-11}}</ref><br><br>
50 years from creation if unpublished, or 50 years from publication (sound records)<ref name="GKRF_1317">{{cite web|url=http://www.consultant.ru/popular/gkrf4/ |title=Article 1317 of Civil Code |publisher=Consultant.ru |date= |accessdate=2014-12-11}}</ref>

70 years from publication (anonymous works)<ref name="GKRF_1281"/>

70 years from publication if published within 70 years from death (posthumous publication)

70 years from publication if published before 3 August 1993 by a corporation (cinematographic, television, radio works, print periodicals and compilations).<ref name="231-FZ"/> Protection term applies to "the whole work" only, i.e. individual authors of each protectable part of the whole work retain their own copyright<ref name="GK_RSFSR_484">Civil Code of the RSFSR, Articles 484-487</ref>

All copyrights to works published prior to [[October Revolution]] (7 November 1917) are believed to be uncopyrighted.
