Engineering in the Americas [[Pre-Columbian era|before the arrival]] of [[Christopher Columbus]] was advanced in [[agriculture]], [[hydrology]], [[irrigation systems]], [[transportation]], [[mechanical engineering]], [[civil engineering]] and [[astronomy]]. In addition [[Indigenous peoples of the Americas|Native Americans]] made extensive use of [[Native American use of fire|fire to change the landscape and to create open areas for farming and hunting]]. Examples of [[pre-Columbian]] engineering from different indigenous civilizations can be found across North and South America.

