[[Image:Ofaerufoss, Sept 1984 (1).jpg|thumb|Ófærufoss with natural bridge in 1984.]]
'''Ófærufoss''' is a [[waterfall]] situated in the [[Eldgjá]] chasm in central [[Iceland]].  Until the early 1990s a [[natural arch|natural bridge]] spanned the falls, but it collapsed from natural causes.<ref>
{{cite web |url=http://volcano.und.edu/vwdocs/volc_images/europe_west_asia/eldgja.html |title=''Eldgja Fissure System, Katla Volcano, Iceland'' |accessdate=2007-08-06 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080308142019/http://volcano.und.edu/vwdocs/volc_images/europe_west_asia/eldgja.html |archivedate=March 8, 2008 |df= }}</ref>

